<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8">
      <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-6">
          <%= image_tag "https://ik.imagekit.io/mthomps4/Avatars/portrait.png", class: "rounded-full w-24 h-24 object-cover border-2 border-slate-300", alt: "Matt Thompson" %>
          <div>
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Matt Thompson</h1>
            <h2 class="text-2xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Software Architect, Craftsman, and Mentor</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 italic">I'm a builder and creator at heart.</p>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
          <p>For over a decade, I've been immersed in software consulting, working across industries including IP Advertising, Healthcare, Telecom, and E-Commerce. I've helped companies understand and solve complex problems while leading teams to drive progress. My focus is on identifying the right problems and fostering team growth. Recognizing that no one should navigate this field alone, I share my experiences and lessons learned to build momentum and mentor others.</p>
          <p>Beyond software, my passion extends into the physical realm of fine woodworking, metalworking, and tool restoration. This pursuit is more than a hobby; it's a commitment to preserving and honing a craft passed down through generations prior. Similar to my approach with software development, I aim to mentor others in resourcefulness and cultivating their own craft (whatever that may be). By curating books, articles, and resources, I share the lessons gathered along the way and stay inspired to pass on a legacy of learning to those interested.</p>
          <p>Who knows? Maybe one day, I'll bridge the gap between traditional craftsmanship and modern technology. (AI and Robotics, anyone?) While my blog focuses primarily on Software Development, follow along for all the twists and turns I take practicing one's craft.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <%= link_to "Connect with me", connect_path, class: "px-6 py-3 text-base rounded-lg bg-slate-100 hover:bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 text-slate-900 dark:text-white" %>
          <%= link_to blog_path, class: "px-6 py-3 text-base rounded-lg bg-green-300 hover:bg-green-400 text-slate-800 flex items-center gap-2" do %>
            To the Blog
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M3 10a.75.75 0 01.75-.75h10.638L10.23 5.29a.75.75 0 111.04-1.08l5.5 5.25a.75.75 0 010 1.08l-5.5 5.25a.75.75 0 11-1.04-1.08l4.158-3.96H3.75A.75.75 0 013 10z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- Features Section -->
    <div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg grid grid-rows-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M2.25 6a3 3 0 013-3h13.5a3 3 0 013 3v12a3 3 0 01-3 3H5.25a3 3 0 01-3-3V6zm3.97.97a.75.75 0 011.06 0l2.25 2.25a.75.75 0 010 1.06l-2.25 2.25a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l1.72-1.72-1.72-1.72a.75.75 0 010-1.06zm4.28 4.28a.75.75 0 000 1.5h3a.75.75 0 000-1.5h-3z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">The Engineer</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">With over a decade of experience, join me as I navigate the highs and lows of software engineering. From getting "Up and Running" to delving into Leadership and Management, this space is for anyone intrigued by the world of tech.</p>
          <%= image_tag "https://ik.imagekit.io/mthomps4/site/tr:w-500,h-500,e-grayscale/split-key.jpg", class: "rounded-lg w-full aspect-square object-cover", alt: "Mechanical Keyboard" %>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg grid grid-rows-[auto_1fr_auto] gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" class="w-6 h-6 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 6.75a5.25 5.25 0 016.775-5.025.75.75 0 01.313 1.248l-3.32 3.319c.063.475.276.934.641 1.299.365.365.824.578 1.3.64l3.318-3.319a.75.75 0 011.248.313 5.25 5.25 0 01-5.472 6.756c-1.018-.086-1.87.1-2.309.634L7.344 21.3A3.298 3.298 0 112.7 16.657l8.684-7.151c.533-.44.72-1.291.634-2.309A5.342 5.342 0 0112 6.75zM4.117 19.125a.75.75 0 01.75-.75h.008a.75.75 0 01.75.75v.008a.75.75 0 01-.75.75h-.008a.75.75 0 01-.75-.75v-.008z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">The Craftsman</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">If you're drawn to the art of fine woodworking, design, and random shop projects, this is your spot. Join me as I share insights from my own journey, along with a growing collection of resources that inspire and guide my craft.</p>
          <%= image_tag "https://ik.imagekit.io/mthomps4/site/tr:w-500,h-500,e-grayscale/handplane.png", class: "rounded-lg w-full aspect-square object-cover", alt: "Wooden Handplane" %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
